comments: Bates-Diop (SAS) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Bridges (PHX) raises both arms as he starts to cut and marginal arm contact occurs with Johnson (SAS) as they engage off-ball.
Johnson (PHX) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.

Paul (PHX) lifts his pivot foot. This is a violation. However, it requires enhanced tools to identify on video and/or does not meet the threshold of observability. Enhanced Review violations will be noted if/when seen in the normal course of game reviews, but are not searched for. The Competition Committee will study these types of plays separately under a different data collection and analysis process. The capture of these plays is variable and should not be counted among totals.
Sochan (SAS) extends both hands into Ayton's (PHX) back and the contact affects his ability to pursue the rebound.

Replay review of the foul called on Sochan (SAS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Sochan (SAS) makes contact with the ball and dislodges it from Paul (PHX) during his rip-through.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in Craig's (PHX) path and marginal contact occurs as he moves towards the basket.
Craig (PHX) steps into Johnson's (SAS) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Craig (PHX) brings his arm forward as he contests and initiates arm contact with Johnson (SAS) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Paul (PHX) reaches in as Poeltl (SAS) secures the rebound and marginal contact occurs before Paul pulls his arm away and Poeltl enters a shooting motion.
Johnson (PHX) legally contests Johnson's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
